<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397388>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. A–F. Trypostega richardi n. sp. A. Group of ovicelled and non-ovicelled autozooids and zooeciules (SAMC- A026788) (scale bar = 0.2 mm, magnified x250). B. Close-up of two zooids, one ovicelled. Note the dimorphic orifice in the ovicelled zooid (SAMC-A026788) (scale bar = 0.2 mm, magnified x400). C. Close-up of an ovicell with circular opening of the associated zooeciule (SAMC-A026788) (scale bar = 0.1 mm, magnified x1.0K). D. Cleithridiate orifice with operculum (SAMC-A026788) (scale bar = 0.05 mm, magnified x1.8K). E. Cleithridiate orifice from an angle showing detail of condyles (SAMC-A028976) (scale bar = 0.05 mm, magnified x350). F. Close-up of two zooeciules (SAMC-A028976) (scale bar = 0.1 mm, magnified x200)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4397388/files/figure.png" .

